In the gay and lesbian community, the term '''U-Haul''' is used to describe a relationship that becomes very close  very fast, for example moving in together after only a short period of time -- a pattern [[stereotype|stereotypically]] attributed to relationships between two women. <ref>[http://www.metroweekly.com/gauge/commentary.php?ak=2225 Metro Weekly]</ref> <ref>[http://www.houstonvoice.com/2006/7-8/view/opinion/brown.cfm Houston Voice]</ref>. The reference to a "U-haul" in the gay community has been considered one of the ''touchstones of sexual identity''. <ref>[http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1589/is_2003_August_19/ai_n6179755 The Advocate August 19th, 2003]</ref> 

The word [[U-Haul]] comes from the popular moving equipment rental company, in reference to the couple moving in to live together after only a few dates. The expression may have been originated by comic [[Lea DeLaria]], who wrote the following joke in the early 1980s:
:''Q: What does a lesbian bring on a second date?''
:''A: A U-Haul.''

The joke has been repeated numerous times <ref>[http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1589/is_2000_Feb_1/ai_59086784 The Advocate, Feb 1st, 2000]</ref> <ref>[http://www.thestranger.com/seattle/Content?oid=14967 The Stranger Jul 17 - Jul 23, 2003]</ref> and is considered a staple in the [[Lesbian Humor]]. <ref>[http://www.sitlec.unibo.it/ishs2002/abstracts_2/Bing.doc "How many lesbians does it take to screw in a light bulb?" An Analysis of Lesbian Humor]</ref>

==Impact on Lesbian Relationships==
It has been theorized that the "U-Haul" phenomenon is used by Lesbians as an escape from the risks involved with dating. <ref>[http://www.kalimunro.com/article_uhaul.html Kali Munro, M.Ed ,''Lesbian Dating: Life Before the U-Haul'']</ref> Despite the appearance that Lesbians do not have difficulties committing to relationships, most experts agree that this behavior is not healthy. <ref>[http://www.seattleweekly.com/news/0425/040623_diversions_ninashapiro.php Seattle Weekly June 23, 2004]</ref>
 

